{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2018-06-30-debugging-4/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"John D Potts","author":"John Potts"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"710a6cf4-e41b-5586-a771-623a98427d4c","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/3acf0/debugging4.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Debugging\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/65f94/debugging4.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/d2682/debugging4.jpg 105w,\n/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/60342/debugging4.jpg 210w,\n/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/65f94/debugging4.jpg 420w,\n/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/828fb/debugging4.jpg 630w,\n/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/bba1f/debugging4.jpg 840w,\n/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/3acf0/debugging4.jpg 2000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The network tab in Chrome dev tools offers a number of troubleshooting helpers for sniffing out problems with page load and network requests.\nThis tab displays a waterfall detailing how long a page takes to load, and the time each resource contributes to that load time.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/19a15/waterfall.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 53.333333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Network Tab\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/d10fb/waterfall.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/79c17/waterfall.png 105w,\n/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/65ed1/waterfall.png 210w,\n/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/d10fb/waterfall.png 420w,\n/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/f058b/waterfall.png 630w,\n/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/1e088/waterfall.png 840w,\n/static/7aaf39eb17f7c1f7107f0a9f1b81aa0a/19a15/waterfall.png 1229w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>You can see if large JS files, images, or other large requests are causing your page speed to lag. You can also view snapshots with a visual history of your page load in this tab.</p>\n<p>Another useful feature of the network tab is the ability to view a site while simulating a slow connection. The downward arrow at the far left lets the user select from a number of speeds; try selecting <code class=\"language-text\">slow 3g</code> and reloading the page- this is how the page loads for users with slow 3G connections.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2/4651d/speed.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 307px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 73.33333333333334%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Network throttle\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2/4651d/speed.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2/79c17/speed.png 105w,\n/static/91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2/65ed1/speed.png 210w,\n/static/91dcf21292b7ad175683281bc2939ba2/4651d/speed.png 307w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 307px) 100vw, 307px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The network tab also gives a ton of details about network requests that are being made. You can filter requests by type, view request and response headers for a particular request, and the timing of that request.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/b3ad9/headers.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 420px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 35.23809523809524%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Headers Tab\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/d10fb/headers.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/79c17/headers.png 105w,\n/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/65ed1/headers.png 210w,\n/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/d10fb/headers.png 420w,\n/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/f058b/headers.png 630w,\n/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/1e088/headers.png 840w,\n/static/91f0981ef4cb7396a9cca6f080bfa71e/b3ad9/headers.png 909w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p> You can also choose to block a particular request or domain and reload the page, simulating the outage of an API.</p>\n<p>This concludes my four-part series on Dev tools: stay tuned for another post coming soon that will detail some of the lesser-known tabs in Chrome Dev Tools!</p>","excerpt":"The network tab in Chrome dev tools offers a number of troubleshooting helpers for sniffing out problems with page load and network requests…","fields":{"slug":"/2018-06-30-debugging-4/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Front End Debugging 4: Network Tab and More","date":"June 30, 2018","recommended":null,"featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"src":"/static/64465d2cb3318fd52c3dae90e7394015/a7715/debugging4.jpg"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2018-06-30-debugging-4/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-06-23-debugging-3/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Front End Debugging: Working with Javascript in Chrome Dev Tools"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018-07-07-cron-jobs/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"A Three-Minute Guide to Cron Jobs"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2913751889"]}